# Finger Mapping Plan

## Goal Description
Switch from a "virtual spatial piano" to a "data glove" style interaction where each finger plays a specific note regardless of position.

## User Review Required
None.

## Proposed Changes
### files
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py)
- **Data Structures**:
    - `NOTE_MAP`: Nested dict `{'Left': {'Pinky': {'Natural': 'C', 'Sharp': 'C#'}, ...}, ...}`.
- **Logic**:
    - Remove `piano_resized`, `piano_overlay`, `KEY_WIDTH_RATIO`.
    - Loop logic:
        - Get Handedness (`Left` or `Right`).
        - For each finger:
            - Calculate Velocity -> Check `VELOCITY_THRESHOLD`.
            - If Trigger:
                - Calculate Angle ([calculate_angle](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py#51-64)).
                - If Angle < 150 (Curled) -> Play Sharp.
                - Else (Straight) -> Play Natural.
- **Visuals**:
    - Floating text at fingertip: "C#!" or "C!".
    - No bottom bar.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Run the app.
- Tap Left Pinky -> Hear C.
- Curl Left Pinky and Tap -> Hear C#.
- Check all 10 fingers.
